Members of Congress from various states and political parties have expressed their support for President Trump's decision to lift metal tariffs on Canada and Mexico. They believe that this move is a significant step towards ratifying the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA) and will benefit industries such as agriculture, manufacturing, and automotive. State and local officials, as well as advocacy and policy organizations, have also voiced their approval, stating that the removal of tariffs will strengthen trade relationships and promote economic growth.